<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="rules-of-respect-and-courtesy-in-communication-with-turkish-professors">Rules of Respect and Courtesy in Communication with Turkish Professors</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">In Turkish culture, respect and courtesy are the cornerstones of communication. There are some important rules to follow when approaching your professors:</p>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li><strong data-start="84" data-end="99">Greetings:</strong> Using phrases like &#8220;Hello&#8221; or &#8220;Mr. Hodja&#8221; when addressing your professors shows respect.</li>



<li><strong data-start="213" data-end="237">Using Polite Language:</strong> Using polite and courteous language in communication increases mutual respect. For example, it would be more respectful to say, &#8220;I would like to talk to you about this.&#8221;</li>



<li><strong data-start="405" data-end="417" data-is-only-node="">Listening:</strong> Listening carefully to what your professors say shows that you value their opinions.</li>



<li><strong data-start="522" data-end="540">Thank you:</strong> Saying thank you after an interview or conversation strengthens your communication. For example, &#8220;Thank you for your time&#8221; will be well received by your professors.</li>



<li><strong data-start="723" data-end="745">Clear and Clear Expression:</strong> When speaking or emailing, expressing your thoughts in a clear and direct way makes communication easier. Avoiding unnecessary details helps you and your instructor to use your time efficiently.</li>



<li><strong data-start="950" data-end="973">Choosing a Suitable Time:</strong> Choosing a suitable time to talk to your professors shows that you are mindful of their busy schedule. It will be more convenient to communicate between classes or during office hours. Or you can send an e-mail in advance to find out the available time interval of your teacher and go to your teacher. This will make you look more professional.</li>



<li><strong data-start="1149" data-end="1178">Eye Contact and Body Language:</strong> Making eye contact and respectful body language in face-to-face communication creates a reassuring effect.</li>
</ul>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">These rules will strengthen your communication with Turkish teachers and help you build a healthier relationship.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">In this topic <a href="https://roadtostudy.com/en/tips-for-making-friends-in-turkey/">Making Friends in Turkey: You can also benefit from our article on Social Mediums and Tips</a>.</p>



