<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="in-class">In Class</h3>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li>Do not speak in class without taking the floor, avoid interrupting the teacher.</li>



<li>Do not talk about irrelevant topics, do not disrupt the flow of the lesson.</li>



<li>A respectful language is used in the classroom.</li>
</ul>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="in-face-to-face-communication">In Face-to-Face Communication</h3>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li>When talking to the teacher, the address &#8220;you&#8221; is always preferred.</li>



<li>If you want to go to the teacher&#8217;s room, you first knock on the door, and if you say &#8220;welcome&#8221;, you enter.</li>



<li>Pay attention to the rules of courtesy during the interview, convey the subject clearly.</li>
</ul>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="mail-communication">Mail Communication</h3>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li>When sending mail, a mail address bearing your own name should be used.</li>



<li>In the input of the e-mail: name, surname, student number, class information should be written.</li>



<li>The request or question in the e-mail should be expressed clearly and understandably.</li>



<li>Mails should be sent during working hours.</li>



<li>Mail should be the priority in communication with the teacher; telephone should be preferred only in emergencies.</li>
</ul>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">With these methods, you can make your communication with your Turkish professors more effective and respectful.</p>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="expectations-of-turkish-professors-what-they-want-from-students">Expectations of Turkish Professors: What They Want from Students</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Turkish professors&#8217; expectations from their students are very important for a healthy education process. Here are some key elements your professors expect from you:</p>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
