<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Tipping taxi drivers is not mandatory in Turkey, but it is a polite custom to round up the fare.<sup></sup> For example, if the ride costs 185 TL, handing over 200 TL and telling the driver to keep the change is standard.<sup></sup> For longer rides or if they help with luggage, a small extra amount (20-50 TL) is appreciated.<sup></sup></p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading">Is 2 euro a good tip in Turkey?</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">While the value of 2 Euros (approx. 75-80 TL) is a generous tip for hotel porters or housekeeping, <strong>avoid giving foreign coins</strong>.<sup></sup> Exchange offices and banks in Turkey generally do not accept foreign coins, making them useless for staff.<sup></sup> It is much better to tip the equivalent amount in Turkish Lira banknotes.<sup></sup></p>', '$.wp_published_at', '2026-01-01T12:10:19Z', '$.wp_modified_at', '2026-03-15T18:39:54Z', '$.featured_image', json('{"provider":"external","src":"/wp-content/uploads/2025/08/taxi-usage-and-tips-guide-in-turkiye.webp","alt":"Yellow car speeding on a blurred coastal road in Turkey","title":"taxi-usage-and-tips-guide-in-turkiye"}')) WHERE "collection" = 'posts' AND "id" = ( SELECT "live_revision_id" FROM "ec_posts" WHERE "deleted_at" IS NULL AND "status" = 'published' AND "locale" = 'en' AND "slug" = 'taxi-usage-tips-in-turkiye' );
