<p class="wp-block-paragraph">The most common greeting is <strong>&#8220;Merhaba&#8221;</strong> (Hello). Close friends and relatives greet with kisses on both cheeks (starting right)<sup>.</sup> A polite <strong>handshake</strong> is usual in formal settings.</p>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading">Do Turks say <em>salam alaikum</em>?</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph"><strong>No</strong>, it is not a standard Turkish greeting. The standard is <strong>&#8220;Merhaba&#8221;</strong> (Hello) or <strong>&#8220;Selam&#8221;</strong> (Peace/Hi) among younger people. <em>Selamün Aleyküm</em> is sometimes used in religious or very conservative contexts.</p>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading">How to address someone respectfully in Turkish?</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Use <strong>&#8220;Bey&#8221;</strong> (for men) or <strong>&#8220;Hanım&#8221;</strong> (for women) after their first name, e.g., <strong>Ali Bey</strong> or <strong>Ayşe Hanım</strong>. Respect elders by using <strong>&#8220;Amca&#8221;</strong> (Uncle) or <strong>&#8220;Teyze&#8221;</strong> (Auntie) even if not related.</p>', '$.wp_published_at', '2025-10-02T12:33:48Z', '$.wp_modified_at', '2026-03-15T18:40:46Z', '$.featured_image', json('{"provider":"external","src":"/wp-content/uploads/2025/08/greeting-and-introduction-etiquette-guide-in-turkiye.webp","alt":"Two people greeting from a distance on a traditional street with a warm hand gesture.","title":"greeting-and-introduction-etiquette-guide-in-turkiye"}')) WHERE "collection" = 'posts' AND "id" = ( SELECT "live_revision_id" FROM "ec_posts" WHERE "deleted_at" IS NULL AND "status" = 'published' AND "locale" = 'en' AND "slug" = 'greeting-and-introductions-in-turkey' );
